rowds, uniforms and street corners replace trenches, and the photographer’s attention shifts to faces and gestures. Later rooms widen into post-war assignments and friendships, including Pablo Picasso at the beach in Golfe-Juan (1948), where fame reads as informal, even awkward, under direct flash and midday sun.</p>\\n<p>A hidden gem is the small group of colour transparencies and lesser-known portraits, hung with restraint to keep looking slow. The final section touches on the founding of Magnum Photos in 1947 and the ongoing afterlife of the archive, including stamps, annotations and publication notes that complicate the idea of a single icon. Running in Madrid, Spain, from 2 October 2025 to 25 January 2026, the full circuit rewards an unhurried 90 minutes.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- copy includes part of the venue postal address\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
