2026-01-23 14:27:03,738 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-643d8b5e-26d5-4178-873f-0f8a2e252f54', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Robert Capa. ICONS, Exhibition, Círculo de Bellas Artes, Madrid: 2 October 2025-25 January 2026\n- short_en: Compare wartime negatives with magazine spreads and contact sheets, tracing how photojournalism images become icons in Madrid.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Inside the galleries at Círculo de Bellas Artes, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context. Prints, contact sheets and editorial layouts sit side by side, so the shift from urgent capture to public image stays visible. Wall texts keep dates and places tight, while quieter vitrines hold working tools that anchor the photographs in daily practice.</p><p>The opening rooms focus on the Spanish Civil War and the ethics of proximity. A highlight is The Falling Soldier (Cerro Muriano, 1936), presented with surrounding frames that emphasise sequencing rather than a single decisive moment. In Madrid, that section lands with particular force, as bombed streets, militia drills and civilian flight read as documentary record rather than distant history. Do not miss the pairing of battlefield photographs with press captions that reveal how meaning changes in print.</p><p>World War II drives the pace up, with images made under pressure and often under restriction. The blurred, salt-stained D-Day photographs from Omaha Beach (6 June 1944) form one of the most direct encounters with danger and mechanical limits. Do not miss the contact sheets that keep rejected frames in view, including crop marks and grease-pencil edits that show decisions at the desk as clearly as decisions in the field. A run of magazine spreads from Life and Picture Post tracks the same images as they circulate.</p><p>Paris reappears in scenes from the Liberation (August 1944), where crowds, uniforms and street corners replace trenches, and the photographer’s attention shifts to faces and gestures. Later rooms widen into post-war assignments and friendships, including Pablo Picasso at the beach in Golfe-Juan (1948), where fame reads as informal, even awkward, under direct flash and midday sun.</p><p>A hidden gem is the small group of colour transparencies and lesser-known portraits, hung with restraint to keep looking slow. The final section touches on the founding of Magnum Photos in 1947 and the ongoing afterlife of the archive, including stamps, annotations and publication notes that complicate the idea of a single “icon”. On view at Círculo de Bellas Artes in Madrid, Spain, from 2 October 2025 to 25 January 2026, with a suggested visit duration of 90 minutes.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
