2026-01-23 14:28:10,391 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-e9e6b3ad-7957-45ed-82bb-26db08b6a667', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: ¡Aquí hay petróleo!, Exhibition, Círculo de Bellas Artes, Madrid: 7 November 2025-8 February 2026\n- short_en: Compare drilling dreams and propaganda in Madrid through maps, posters and newsreels, and trace how oil shapes politics, labour and daily routines.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Inside the galleries at Círculo de Bellas Artes, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context. ¡Aquí hay petróleo! follows the hunt for crude oil as science, industry and state messaging, then tracks what that hunt does to work, transport and domestic life. The route reads clearly in about 60 minutes, with tight transitions from survey to extraction to public image.</p><p>The opening rooms insist on measurement before myth. A highlight is a wall-sized geological map, crowded with drill targets, hand-inked corrections and pencilled depth notes that turn uncertainty into a plan. Nearby, seismic survey diagrams and stratigraphic columns compress kilometres of rock into clean lines, while telegrams, permits and typed memoranda reveal how quickly technical language becomes administrative instruction. A small display of sample vials and sand trays links those abstractions back to grit, weight and colour.</p><p>Don’t miss the run of CAMPSA advertising posters, where tankers, refinery stacks and pump attendants deliver reassurance through hard geometry, limited palettes and blunt slogans. The posters sit beside price lists and ration notices, forcing a comparison between promise and procurement. Another don’t-miss element is the NO-DO newsreel montage: choreographed machinery, staged inaugurations and tidy crowds, cut into a loop that makes extraction feel orderly and inevitable. The editing rhythm matters as much as the images, turning drills and pipelines into a national routine.</p><p>Material from the Ayoluengo well in La Lora grounds the story in labour and maintenance. A labelled core sample and worn drill fragments sit alongside shift rosters, safety notices and canteen rules, pulling attention from rhetoric to daily risk. Photographs of rigs at dusk, temporary barracks and muddy access roads tighten the focus on logistics, fatigue and the social world built around a single wellhead.</p><p>A hidden gem waits in a narrow case of field paperwork: a geologist’s pocket notebook packed with quick section sketches, depth figures and weather notes, the paper edges darkened by repeated handling. Press clippings and parliamentary extracts nearby show the same data travelling upward, first as cautious technical phrasing and then as certainty. On view from 7 November 2025 to 8 February 2026, the final wall pairs import statistics with household receipts for paraffin and petrol.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
