2026-01-23 14:28:12,397 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-3818d3ea-331a-4c54-a7ba-5ff97906f56f', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: La casa de las artes. Abierta desde 1926, Círculo de Bellas Artes, Madrid\n- Venue: Círculo de Bellas Artes\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Círculo de Bellas Artes, C/ Alcalá, 42, 28014 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2026-02-12 to 2026-05-10\n- Suggested visit duration: 60 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: In the first rooms at Círculo de Bellas Artes, close looking matters as objects and images do the work.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Handle\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Handle a century of Círculo stories, trace voices through posters and programmes, and follow art networks across an hour’s careful reading.", "long": "<p>In the first rooms at Círculo de Bellas Artes, close looking matters as objects and images do the work. Paper, paint, and architectural traces map how an institution opened its doors in 1926 and kept widening its cultural remit through talks, exhibitions, performances, and social life. The presentation stays alert to the mechanics of making art public, who signed up, who spoke, who printed, who paid, and who queued.</p>\\n<p>A clear highlight sits at the centre, material tied to architect Antonio Palacios that pins the building to its making. Plans, elevations, and a compact model sharpen the sense of scale and intention, from the façade’s classical discipline to the interior circulation that funnels crowds towards halls and studios. Early photographs fix the same spaces in use, catching stage light, seating banks, and the press of bodies.</p>\\n<p>Don’t miss the 1926 inauguration programme, displayed alongside invitations and a seating plan that turns a ceremonial night into readable logistics. Also don’t miss the dense run of posters and handbills, where typography, ink, and paper quality register changing budgets and urgencies. Together they track concert announcements, lecture series, and exhibitions as quick, physical messages sent into the streets, then pinned, folded, saved, and filed.</p>\\n<p>The exhibition gains force when it slows down over small administrative objects. A membership ledger, stamped cards, and correspondence show the institution as a machine that runs on signatures and decisions, with names, dues, and dates marching across the page. Press cuttings and magazine spreads extend the story beyond the walls, noting openings, arguments, cancellations, and the steady work of publicity. Tickets, seating stubs, and a handful of programme notes bring the social mix into focus, the crowd not as an abstraction but as bodies guided by paper rules.</p>\\n<p>The hidden gem is a modest vitrine of annotated meeting minutes, with crossed out lines and marginal notes that record disagreement, compromise, and the everyday labour behind cultural prestige. A small cluster of backstage photographs rewards slow reading, cables, curtains, and improvised storage hinting at what the public never sees.</p>\\n<p>La casa de las artes. Abierta desde 1926, Círculo de Bellas Artes, Madrid runs from 12 February to 10 May 2026 at Círculo de Bellas Artes. Allow around 60 minutes to move through the rooms, read key documents, and compare images of the building with the printed matter it generated.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- copy includes part of the venue postal address\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
