es and early Shox columns underline how cushioning swings between flexibility, compression and mechanical rebound under load.</p>\\n<p>A highlight comes in the Flyknit zone, where uppers hang like pattern maps and reveal tension shifts, yarn types and seam reduction. Stitch-density swatches mark reinforcement around toe, midfoot and heel, while a colour library ties digital knit files to finished uppers across training and competition palettes. A set of lacing tests and eyelet samples keeps the focus on pressure points and lockdown.</p>\\n<p>Later rooms turn to collaborations and cultural adoption through campaign stills, limited-run releases and athlete-issued objects, including signed spikes, training logs and taped-up laces. A wall of repair and wear, re-glued soles, frayed eyelets and marked insoles, argues for use as evidence. Plan 60 to 90 minutes for the full circuit.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- copy includes part of the venue postal address\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
