2026-01-23 14:32:46,610 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-e0766c79-81af-45c4-b0f2-22c673cd1961', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Exposición, Exhibition, Cosentino City Madrid, Madrid\n- Venue: Cosentino City Madrid\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Cosentino City Madrid, Paseo de la Castellana, 116, 28046 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2026-02-19 to 2026-03-08\n- Suggested visit duration: 45 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: Inside the galleries at Cosentino City Madrid, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Track\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Track material-led installations, process displays and talks at Cosentino City Madrid, then compare finishes side by side in 45 minutes.", "long": "<p>Inside the galleries at Cosentino City Madrid, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context.</p>\\n<p>Running 19 February to 8 March 2026 in Madrid, Spain, Exposición, Exhibition sets a tight sequence of material experiments against drawings, captions and working notes. Large surfaces sit at eye level, then drop into tables of offcuts, test pieces and tooling marks, so decisions read clearly, from raw cut to finished edge.</p>\\n<p>Highlight: a room-scale slab installation, “Castellana Grid”, uses alternating matte and polished panels to change the light as bodies pass, turning a simple walk into a shifting pattern of glare and shadow. Nearby, a long communal table, “Counterpoint”, locks tessellated samples into a single plane and invites close comparison of grain, reflectivity and colour drift.</p>\\n<p>Don’t miss element one: the process wall of annotated CAD prints and taped-up mock-ups, pinned beside the finished panels they describe, with revisions left visible rather than tidied away. Don’t miss element two: “Cut Line”, a short series of documentary photographs by Madrid-based photographer Lucía García, tracking fabrication stages, water-jet cuts, edge profiling and final sealing.</p>\\n<p>Hidden gem: a small drawer unit labelled “Failures” holds cracked corners, misaligned joins and scorched test strips, each tagged with the adjustment that followed. It reads like a lab notebook in three dimensions, and it sharpens the rest of the display by showing what got rejected.</p>\\n<p>Throughout, text stays brief and practical, focusing on thickness, tolerances, join types and finishing methods. Seating sits beside a compact reading table with catalogues, swatch cards and spec sheets for slower looking. Suggested visit duration is 45 minutes.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 265)\n- copy includes part of the venue postal address\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
