2026-01-23 14:33:20,853 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-5c766d50-11f6-4782-9cb1-03df21cfef26', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Transylvanian Design Week, Exhibition, Instituto Cultural Rumano, Madrid\n- Venue: Instituto Cultural Rumano\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Instituto Cultural Rumano, Plaza del Cordón, 1, Bajo derecha, 28005 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2026-02-06 to 2026-03-04\n- Suggested visit duration: 45 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: Across the galleries at Instituto Cultural Rumano, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Track\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Track Transylvanian design through chairs, textiles and graphic prints at Instituto Cultural Rumano, Madrid, in about 45 minutes.", "long": "<p>Across the galleries at Instituto Cultural Rumano, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype. Transylvanian Design Week brings contemporary work from Romania into a tight, readable route in Madrid, running from 6 February to 4 March 2026. The selection keeps its focus on making, showing how hand skills sit beside digital processes without forcing a slogan.</p>\\n<p>A clear highlight is a room of seating prototypes in beech, ash, and laminated plywood, where joints and fasteners stay visible rather than concealed. A low, three-legged stool in steamed beech sits next to a cantilevered chair in bent birch, and the contrast turns construction into the main subject. Grain, tool marks, and edges do the talking, especially when light cuts across the exposed laminations.</p>\\n<p>Don’t miss the textile wall, where woven wool panels and narrow bands of embroidery map patterns associated with Transylvania onto modern formats. One hanging uses natural dyes to move from iron black to rust red in tight steps, while another turns a traditional motif into a near-abstract grid. Nearby, a set of small sample books invites close looking at weave density, thread twist, and the small compromises made for durability.</p>\\n<p>Don’t miss the graphic corner: a screen-printed poster series in limited colours, a set of wayfinding pictograms, and a typographic study that tests diacritics at different sizes. Paper stocks matter here, from soft uncoated sheets to glossy card, and ink coverage shifts the tone from matte to almost metallic. The most direct work keeps text spare and lets spacing carry rhythm.</p>\\n<p>A hidden gem sits on a side plinth, a cluster of glazed ceramic tiles made as test pieces rather than finished products. Fingerprints remain under the glaze, and the firing results range from smoky grey to sharp green where the kiln ran hotter. The tiles sit beside a notebook of recipes and temperature notes, making the small failures as informative as the clean outcomes.</p>\\n<p>Plan around 45 minutes to take in the full route, with extra time for the material samples and process notes that sit low in the cases. In Madrid, the show reads as a working survey rather than a polished statement, with tools, offcuts, and mock-ups kept in view.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- copy includes part of the venue postal address\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
