2026-01-23 14:33:54,391 DEBUG openai._base_client: HTTP Response: POST https://api.openai.com/v1/responses "200 OK" Headers({'date': 'Fri, 23 Jan 2026 10:33:54 GMT', 'content-type': 'application/json', 'transfer-encoding': 'chunked', 'connection': 'keep-alive', 'x-ratelimit-limit-requests': '10000', 'x-ratelimit-limit-tokens': '4000000', 'x-ratelimit-remaining-requests': '9999', 'x-ratelimit-remaining-tokens': '3999138', 'x-ratelimit-reset-requests': '6ms', 'x-ratelimit-reset-tokens': '12ms', 'openai-version': '2020-10-01', 'openai-organization': 'divento', 'openai-project': 'proj_lgr47s5G9zYA1BjFZQpHGMQB', 'x-request-id': 'req_cf80370447284e01b66dcaa360d5c5a9', 'openai-processing-ms': '13805', 'x-envoy-upstream-service-time': '13806', 'cf-cache-status': 'DYNAMIC', 'strict-transport-security': 'max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload', 'x-content-type-options': 'nosniff', 'server': 'cloudflare', 'cf-ray': '9c26a25bfbee4e68-TBS', 'content-encoding': 'gzip', 'alt-svc': 'h3=":443"; ma=86400'})
2026-01-23 14:33:54,392 DEBUG openai._base_client: request_id: req_cf80370447284e01b66dcaa360d5c5a9
2026-01-23 14:33:54,394 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-23160df1-8662-4724-a466-53cb2e8a0380', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Exposición, Exhibition, Cosentino City Madrid: 19 February-8 March 2026\n- short_en: Track material studies and process notes at Cosentino City Madrid, then weigh texture and light across sample walls in 45 minutes.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Inside the galleries at Cosentino City Madrid, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context. It runs from 19 February to 8 March 2026 and keeps the pace brisk, shifting between large installed surfaces and the hand-scale evidence of how they were made. Sightlines stay open, so reflections and joins can be judged from across the room before the route drops into close looking.</p><p>At the centre is a sequence of full-height panels in engineered stone and ultra-compact surfaces, hung to make thickness, edge choices and fixing points legible. Labels stay practical, listing cut directions, polishing stages, sealants and tolerance notes. A narrow table carries offcuts, drill tests and corner mitres, each marked with pencil measurements that mirror the wall labels, turning specification into something tangible.</p><p>Highlight: the room-scale slab installation “Castellana Grid” sets alternating matte and polished planes into a strict rhythm, so light changes as people move past and a grid seems to pulse without any mechanics. Beside it, “Counterpoint” compresses tessellated samples into a single long plane, where shifts in grain, reflectivity and undertone show up under the same lighting.</p><p>Don’t miss element one: the process wall of annotated CAD prints, taped mock-ups and rejected revisions, pinned beside the finished panels they describe, with crossings-out left in place. The edits make the material decisions easier to read, from seam placement to the final edge radius. Don’t miss element two: “Cut Line”, a short documentary photo series by Madrid-based photographer Lucía García, tracking water-jet cuts, edge profiling, dry fits and sealing, with timestamps that align to the objects on display.</p><p>Hidden gem: a low drawer unit labelled “Failures” holds cracked corners, scorched test strips and misaligned joins, each tagged with the adjustment that followed and the tool that caused the error. It sharpens the rest of the route by showing what gets discarded and why, without dressing it up as a lesson.</p><p>A compact reading table gathers spec sheets, swatch cards, adhesive samples and a small “Edge Library” of finished profiles, bullnose, bevel and pencil, set beside a single lamp for controlled light. Suggested visit duration is 45 minutes, with a shorter loop possible by skipping the reading table and returning for the drawers.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
