2026-01-23 14:34:26,297 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-c8cb7878-9fb3-4fd5-87af-b36799527b1a', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Transylvanian Design Week, Exhibition, Instituto Cultural Rumano, Madrid: 6 February-4 March 2026\n- short_en: Track Transylvanian design through chairs, textiles and graphic prints at Instituto Cultural Rumano, Madrid, in about 45 minutes.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Across the galleries at Instituto Cultural Rumano, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype. Transylvanian Design Week brings contemporary work from Romania into a tight, readable route in Madrid, running from 6 February to 4 March 2026. The selection keeps its focus on making, showing how hand skills sit beside digital processes without forcing a slogan.</p><p>A clear highlight is a room of seating prototypes in beech, ash, and laminated plywood, where joints and fasteners stay visible rather than concealed. A low, three-legged stool in steamed beech sits next to a cantilevered chair in bent birch, and the contrast turns construction into the main subject. Grain, tool marks, and edges do the talking, especially when light cuts across the exposed laminations.</p><p>Don’t miss the textile wall, where woven wool panels and narrow bands of embroidery map patterns associated with Transylvania onto modern formats. One hanging uses natural dyes to move from iron black to rust red in tight steps, while another turns a traditional motif into a near-abstract grid. Nearby, a set of small sample books invites close looking at weave density, thread twist, and the small compromises made for durability.</p><p>Don’t miss the graphic corner: a screen-printed poster series in limited colours, a set of wayfinding pictograms, and a typographic study that tests diacritics at different sizes. Paper stocks matter here, from soft uncoated sheets to glossy card, and ink coverage shifts the tone from matte to almost metallic. The most direct work keeps text spare and lets spacing carry rhythm.</p><p>A hidden gem sits on a side plinth, a cluster of glazed ceramic tiles made as test pieces rather than finished products. Fingerprints remain under the glaze, and the firing results range from smoky grey to sharp green where the kiln ran hotter. The tiles sit beside a notebook of recipes and temperature notes, making the small failures as informative as the clean outcomes.</p><p>Plan around 45 minutes to take in the full route, with extra time for the material samples and process notes that sit low in the cases. In Madrid, the show reads as a working survey rather than a polished statement, with tools, offcuts, and mock-ups kept in view.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
