2026-01-23 14:36:08,990 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-87928b7a-11df-4e89-b2e2-02232cc33bfb', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Pieza del mes, Exhibition, Museo de Historia de Madrid: 3 March-31 March 2026\n- short_en: Watch one Madrid object get the full treatment, with crisp context notes, archival images, and a brisk 30 minute stop at the museum.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>Across the galleries at Museo de Historia de Madrid, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype. Pieza del mes keeps the scale tight and the focus sharp: one object, a small set of supporting documents, and clear wall text that favours evidence over grand claims. The result rewards slow looking, from paper fibres and tool marks to the civic stamps and handwritten numbers that usually get ignored in a crowded case.</p><p>The highlight in March is an albumen photograph by Jean Laurent that frames Madrid as a working city rather than a postcard. Stone façades read as surfaces with scars, shop signs pull the eye to street level, and a thin line of traffic hints at changing habits of movement. The print’s tonal range matters here, with deep shadows under balconies and a pale sky that leaves architecture to do the work.</p><p>One don’t-miss element is the side-by-side comparison with a wall-sized reproduction of Pedro Texeira’s 1656 map of Madrid, used as a visual anchor for street layout and naming. The pairing makes urban change legible without resorting to sweeping statements. A second don’t-miss is the magnification station, which brings out retouching on the negative, edge wear from handling, and the photographer’s numbering system along the margin.</p><p>A hidden gem sits in plain sight: the verso details. Faint pencil notes, a collector’s mark, and a small paper repair turn the photograph into a travelled object with its own biography. Nearby context points beyond the case: León Gil de Palacio’s 1830 scale model of Madrid, seen in the museum’s rooms, helps translate the photograph’s flat planes into volumes, heights, and routes, with rooftops and courtyards snapping into place.</p><p>Running from 3 to 31 March 2026, the display fits a 30 minute circuit, including time to read the object label in full and return for a second look after the map comparison. Text is in Spanish with key terms clarified for non-specialists, and the lighting is tuned to protect the print while keeping surface gloss under control. A final caption calls attention to the pressure mark of an official seal impressed into the paper.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
