start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Chart\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Chart how drawings, comics and sound scripts imagine tomorrow at Casa del Lector in Madrid, in a focused 60-minute circuit.", "long": "<p>Rooms at Casa del Lector map the show’s themes through objects, images, sound and text. Exposición Ómnibus. El futuro se dibuja aquí is running in Madrid, Spain, from 20 November 2025 to 1 February 2026, and it keeps the pace tight, around 60 minutes. The route moves between reading, looking and listening, treating the page as a site for invention and argument rather than decoration.</p>\\n<p>Early sections foreground process. Pencil thumbnails sit beside inked storyboard panels, colour tests and printer’s proofs, so decisions stay visible, cut lines, taped joins and correction fluid included. A sequence of annotated layouts tracks how a single scene shifts through framing and rhythm, while a bank of short texts names the tools, nibs, brushes and software settings that shape the final mark.</p>\\n<p>Highlight: a wall-length collaborative comic strip that grows panel by panel across the rooms, stitching everyday Madrid details into speculative situations. Don’t miss the risograph zine rack, where small-run pamphlets, fold-outs and stapled mini comics form a quick survey of current graphic self-publishing. Don’t miss the sound kiosks either, which pair spoken scripts with projected drawings, letting timing and breath drive the images.</p>\\n<p>Public transport acts as a quiet organising metaphor. Route maps, ticket stubs and timetable graphics appear as source material, then re-emerge as diagrams for imagined cities and alternative futures. Posters and mock book covers test how typography carries tone, and a set of flipbooks turns gesture into motion, one frame at a time, under steady overhead light.</p>\\n<p>Hidden gem: a low drawer of discarded drafts, margins and rejected captions, kept deliberately rough, with notes that argue with themselves. It sits near a small table of materials, acetate sheets, tracing paper, marker pens and binding thread, inviting close looking at wear, pressure and repetition as the true record of thought.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 299)\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
