2026-01-23 14:37:31,000 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-db518f45-f07e-475c-85f7-5860d86cec35', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Generación 2026, Exhibition, La Casa Encendida, Madrid\n- Venue: La Casa Encendida\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Ronda de Valencia, 2, 28012 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2026-01-30 to 2026-04-19\n- Suggested visit duration: 60-90 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: Galleries at La Casa Encendida set out a clear route through materials, techniques and context.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Track\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Track new art in Madrid, moving from film to sculpture and sound at La Casa Encendida, allow 60 to 90 minutes.", "long": "<p>Galleries at La Casa Encendida set out a clear route through materials, techniques and context. Rooms move from tightly edited wall works to floor-based installations, with clear sightlines that let sound, light and texture lead the pace. The selection keeps attention on making processes, edits, joins, cuts, recordings, firings, and on how ideas shift when a work shares space with others.</p>\\n<p>Generación 2026 is on in Madrid, Spain, from 30 January to 19 April 2026. As an annual snapshot of emerging practice, it gathers recent work across moving image, sculpture, drawing, photography and sound, with concise texts that note methods and references rather than slogans. The route reads as a set of propositions about labour, attention and social space, organised to reward close looking as well as quick scanning.</p>\\n<p>A multi-channel sound piece in a dim room sets a steady pulse for the whole hang, this is the highlight for many. Don’t miss the 16 mm film loop that turns a simple gesture into an insistently physical rhythm, nor the floor-based ceramic map whose hairline cracks and repairs become part of its meaning. Nearby, a series of A3 drawings pinned edge-to-edge keeps the hand visible, erasures, smudges and rewritten lines remain in place. A bank of small-format photographs, each printed with a narrow border, asks for slow reading of faces, pavements and thresholds.</p>\\n<p>A hidden gem sits at the reading table, where process notes, zines and working prints offer a second route through the same ideas, and small details (tape marks, marginalia, rejected captions) sharpen what ends up on the walls. Allow 60 to 90 minutes to follow the full sequence and return to the sound room for a second listen, where overlapping voices settle into different patterns from one pass to the next. Quiet benches near the windows suit a pause between the denser installations and the final gallery.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 310)\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
