2026-01-23 14:37:40,848 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-3652e19d-af70-4291-9c7b-e49b19ced41c', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Wunderkammer. Ana Juan, Exhibition, CentroCentro, Madrid: 29 January-3 May 2026\n- short_en: Watch Ana Juan’s ink drawings and paper maquettes at CentroCentro, Madrid, and trace her cabinet-of-curiosities logic in 60 to 90 minutes.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>A sequence of rooms at CentroCentro grounds the show in specific works and practical context. Rather than a straight career survey, the layout treats Ana Juan’s imagery as a working cabinet of curiosities, where repeated motifs, masks, animals and domestic objects accrue meaning through proximity. Running from 29 January to 3 May 2026 in Madrid, Spain, the exhibition keeps attention on process: ideas arrive as pencil notations, sharpen into ink lines, then settle as finished sheets or book-ready compositions. Allow 60 to 90 minutes for an unhurried circuit.</p><p>The first rooms prioritise drawing as an instrument. Ink-and-watercolour works sit near rough pencil studies, making corrections and restarts visible. Small-format pieces reward close looking, especially where washes thin to a stain and the line takes over again. A tighter grouping of preparatory sketches reads like a storyboard, with facial expressions shifting from panel to panel and animals serving as stand-ins for emotional states.</p><p>Highlight: the central cabinet-style arrangement that brings together original drawings, cut-paper elements and small paper maquettes, kept at eye level like specimens. The density matters, it encourages a forensic reading of materials and scale. Don’t miss element one: a set of publication-related works (including covers and spreads) that shows how an image changes when it meets typography, cropping and print constraints. Don’t miss element two: the wall devoted to serial variations, where a single figure reappears across multiple sheets with altered colour, posture and lighting.</p><p>Across the run, the exhibition keeps returning to narrative craft. Book dummies and annotated proofs reveal pacing decisions, page turns and the weight of silence between scenes. Texture carries story as much as plot, with scraped highlights, erasures and stitched-looking marks that suggest wear, memory and repair. The room devoted to darker tonal registers puts shadow to work as structure, not decoration.</p><p>Hidden gem: the back-of-page evidence, taped notes, colour tests, and hand-written cues that survive on mounts and margins, and quietly map the route from idea to final image. The final room holds a quieter cluster of intimate studies, pinned low, with attention drawn to hands, seams and the edges of fabric.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
