2026-01-23 14:38:05,809 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-9503ece3-2d44-4a4d-82de-f07ed8f99c5c', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Madrid Colecciona. 50 colecciones de arte contemporáneo, Exhibition, CentroCentro, Madrid\n- Venue: CentroCentro\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Plaza de Cibeles, 1, 28014 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2026-02-26 to 2026-09-06\n- Suggested visit duration: 90 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: Inside the galleries at CentroCentro, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Listen\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Listen to Madrid’s collectors through paintings, sculpture and archive notes at CentroCentro, a 90-minute circuit of contemporary art.", "long": "<p>Inside the galleries at CentroCentro, the route moves from key works to supporting material and context. Madrid Colecciona gathers art from 50 contemporary collections and sets it in conversation, not as a single canon but as a map of decisions, allegiances and risks taken over time. Paint hangs near sculpture, photographs interrupt painting, and small documentary groupings explain how works entered homes, offices and foundations across the city.</p>\\n\\n<p>The display keeps attention on objects and their provenance. Names such as Antoni Tàpies, Miquel Barceló and Juan Muñoz anchor several rooms, while quieter strands turn to artists’ books, multiples and works on paper. Labels track acquisitions and loans, and vitrines hold catalogues, invitation cards and correspondence, making the collecting process tangible rather than abstract. Material choices matter here, bronze, charcoal, acetate, inkjet print, and the installation order encourages close reading of surfaces and seams.</p>\\n\\n<p>Highlight: a tightly edited sequence of sculpture and installation studies, where maquettes and finished works sit side by side to show scale shifts and fabrication decisions. Do not miss: the photographic wall that moves from staged portraiture to documentary series, then to conceptual image making, with clear comparisons of framing and repetition. Do not miss: the screening corner for time based work, where short films and single channel videos slow the pace and sharpen attention to sound, subtitles and edits.</p>\\n\\n<p>Hidden gem: a small case of ephemera and marginalia, including handwritten checklists, shipping labels, condition notes and annotated floorplans that reveal how collectors organise storage, display and care. The selection also makes room for institutional loans and private holdings in the same sightlines, underlining how taste circulates between public programmes and personal commitments. The exhibition runs in Madrid, Spain, from 26 February 2026 to 6 September 2026, and suits a 90 minute visit.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 296)\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
