2026-01-23 14:39:07,047 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-e8f42da9-4b6b-4b8a-9579-171d98afc574', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Juan Uslé Ese barco en la montaña, Exhibition, Museo Reina Sofía, Madrid\n- Venue: Museo Reina Sofía\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Calle Santa Isabel, 52, 28012 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2025-11-26 to 2026-04-20\n- Suggested visit duration: 60-90 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: In the first rooms at Museo Reina Sofía, close looking matters as objects and images do the work.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'See\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "See Juan Uslé’s nocturnal grids and restless colour at Reina Sofía, where paintings and works on paper reward slow attention.", "long": "<p>In the first rooms at Museo Reina Sofía, close looking matters as objects and images do the work. Juan Uslé builds paintings from repetition, pressure, and small shifts in tone, letting stripes thicken, fade, and return. The result reads like a record of nights spent painting, with colour laid down in measured pulses rather than gestures.</p>\\n<p>Running from 26 November 2025 to 20 April 2026, the exhibition tracks Uslé’s long dialogue with time and place, moving between New York studio discipline and memories of northern Spain. Canvases hang with enough space to register edges, seams, and the way acrylic sits on the surface. A highlight comes in the work titled <em>Ese barco en la montaña</em>, where stacked bands tighten into a steady, almost tidal rhythm.</p>\\n<p>Don’t miss the sequence from <em>Soñé que revelabas</em>, a set of night paintings in which narrow verticals accumulate like beats, and small colour decisions, a bruise of violet, a sudden acidic green, change the temperature of the whole field. Also don’t miss the room that pares the palette back, pushing greys and off-whites until the eye starts to measure gloss, matte, and the pressure of the brush.</p>\\n<p>Works on paper sharpen the sense of process without turning it into explanation. A group of drawings in graphite and ink tests line, wobble, and correction, while a compact suite related to <em>Nudos y Rizomas</em> turns knotting marks into a stubborn, bodily weave. Labels stay light, so attention stays on intervals, overlaps, and the way a repeated mark can suddenly carry weight.</p>\\n<p>A hidden gem sits in the quieter corners: small studies that keep the hand close to the page, where a single band of colour is tried, erased, and tried again. The installation keeps sightlines open, so distant canvases act as anchors while nearby surfaces insist on texture. Suggested visit duration is 60 to 90 minutes.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 311)\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
