2026-01-23 14:39:47,798 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-899b0ba4-5215-4318-a319-aef71199c346', 'json_data': {'input': 'Write copy for a Divento temporary exhibition listing.\n\nINPUTS\n- Title: Maruja Mallo Máscara y compás, Exhibition, Museo Reina Sofía, Madrid\n- Venue: Museo Reina Sofía\n- City: Madrid\n- Country: Spain\n- Address: Calle Santa Isabel, 52, 28012 Madrid, Spain\n- Dates (ISO): 2025-10-08 to 2026-03-16\n- Suggested visit duration: 60-90 minutes\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS (must pass)\n- Write as though the exhibition is already running; do not use future tense.\n- British English spelling.\n- Never use the first person.\n- Do not use these words anywhere: You, visitor, visitors, located, feature, featured, showcase, blend, period, accessible.\n- Do not use em/en dash characters: — or –. If you want that pause, rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Do not include citations, links, or URLs.\n- Do not include the venue’s postal address (no street, postcode, or \'address is …\').\n\nLONG (HTML)\n- 350 to 400 words. Target 380–395 words.\n- If you are under 350 words, add one more factual sentence to reach the minimum.\n- Multiple paragraphs; wrap each paragraph in <p> tags.\n- Do not begin with the exhibition name or \'this exhibition\'.\n- Start the long description (immediately after <p>) with this exact sentence: Across the galleries at Museo Reina Sofía, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype.\n- Avoid concluding sentences.\n- Include naturally: one highlight, two don\'t-miss elements, and one hidden gem.\n- Mention at least three specific works, artists, or items when possible.\n- Use strong verbs, concrete nouns, active voice; cut filler.\n- No brochure-style language, clichés, or exaggerated adjectives.\n\nSHORT\n- Maximum 164 characters.\n- Must include a verb.\n- Must not repeat the exhibition name.\n- Must not repeat the phrasing or start of the long description.\n\n- Start the short description with the exact first word \'Listen\'.\n- Do not start the short description with \'Explore\'.\nOUTPUT\n- Return ONLY a JSON object with exactly the keys \'short\' and \'long\'.\n- Both \'short\' and \'long\' must be non-empty strings.\n\nPREVIOUS OUTPUT (JSON)\n{"short": "Listen as Maruja Mallo’s masks and measured lines speak through paintings, drawings and notebooks that map Madrid modernity in 60 to 90 minutes.", "long": "<p>Across the galleries at Museo Reina Sofía, materials and techniques carry the argument without hype. In Madrid, Spain, Maruja Mallo emerges as a disciplined experimenter whose wit depends on exact edges, calibrated curves and abrupt shifts of scale. The show runs from 8 October 2025 to 16 March 2026 and keeps attention on how a picture is built, not on mythmaking around a single name.</p>\\n<p>The title’s two poles, máscara and compás, organise the route. Masks appear as social armour, carnival skin, and hard geometry, while the compass turns up as a working method, in arcs, grids and measured diagonals. Paint, paper, and collage sit side by side so that decisions of support and surface read as clearly as subject matter.</p>\\n<p>A clear highlight is <i>La verbena</i> (1927), where crowd movement locks into a taut, almost architectural rhythm. One don’t miss element follows in the acid bite of <i>Cloacas y campanarios</i> (c.1930), a set of works that refuses the picturesque and pushes the city into satire and anatomy. Another don’t miss element is <i>La sorpresa del trigo</i> (1936), which shifts the register again, tightening volume and light into a poised, almost ceremonial stillness.</p>\\n<p>The hanging makes space for preparatory labour. Studies, painted maquettes and annotated sheets show how curves become structure and how humour survives revision. Close looking rewards the eye in pencil pressure, erased construction lines, and the way pigments thin out at the edges to expose the weave of paper or the tooth of ground.</p>\\n<p>A hidden gem sits in the small-scale material: a notebook page with compass pricks and clipped fragments, kept near documentary photographs and correspondence that trace friendships and professional negotiations without sentimental gloss. A typical circuit takes 60 to 90 minutes, with room texts keeping the focus on decisions of line, scale, and surface.</p>"}\n\nFix these issues:\n- long word count must be 350–400 (got 300)\nReturn ONLY the corrected JSON object.\n', 'max_output_tokens': 2500, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_exhibition_copy', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['short', 'long']}}}}}
