2026-01-23 14:40:19,880 DEBUG openai._base_client: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/responses', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-87c49d7d-6e4a-469d-b415-ff5d68ef7b1d', 'json_data': {'input': "Translate the following Divento temporary exhibition content.\n\nRules (follow exactly):\n- Return ONLY a JSON object matching the provided schema.\n- Do not add citations, links, or URLs.\n- Avoid em/en dash characters (— or –); rewrite with commas or parentheses.\n- Keep all HTML tags intact in 'long' and return valid HTML.\n- Do NOT add extra blank lines/newlines.\n- For 'short': maximum 164 characters in the target language, keep natural phrasing.\n- For 'name': translate only what should be translated; keep proper nouns/titles as appropriate.\n- For zh-CN: translate ALL prose into Simplified Chinese; Latin script is allowed ONLY for proper nouns and official artwork/series titles.\n\nEnglish inputs:\n- name_en: Andrea Canepa Fardo, Exhibition, Museo Reina Sofía, Madrid: 13 January 2026-1 January 2027\n- short_en: Unpick bundled matter, rubbed textures, and tight sound cues at Museo Reina Sofía, a focused 45 to 60 minutes of measured tension.\nlong_en_html:\n<p>A sequence of rooms at Museo Reina Sofía grounds the show in specific works and practical context. In Madrid, Andrea Canepa tests how an artwork carries weight, literally in bundled matter and figuratively in memory, labour, and the routes objects take through hands. The run (13 January 2026 to 1 January 2027) supports repeat viewing, but a single pass holds together in 45 to 60 minutes. Sightlines stay controlled, and the pacing shifts between open floor and compressed thresholds.</p><p>The entry sets a restrained tempo: paper, fabric, and wood meet disciplined light and clean edges. A central object, a tightly wrapped hessian load titled <i>Fardo</i>, anchors the first room and acts as a hinge for what follows. Along one wall, graphite rubbings lift texture from everyday surfaces, turning scuffs and grain into a kind of evidence. A low plinth with small offcuts and fasteners keeps attention on method, not polish.</p><p>A highlight arrives in the sound room, where a four-channel audio work uses breath, steps, and clipped phrases to pull attention away from the walls and into the body. The volume never swells into spectacle, it keeps to pressure and pause. One don’t-miss element is the set of annotated notebooks under glass, dense with measurements, diagrams, and crossed-out decisions that clarify how larger forms are built. Another don’t-miss element sits opposite, a small projection of hand movements, slowed to near stillness, that makes simple actions read as ritual.</p><p>Material choices keep doing the talking. Rope bites into cloth, staples hold seams, and rough timber frames refuse to disappear behind the idea of “finish”. A line of pinned templates and measured drawings reads like a working grammar for the bundled forms. The internal logic becomes clearest in the transition corridor, where contact sheets and working photographs trace the same object through different rooms and lighting conditions, insisting on repetition as method rather than decoration. A narrow bench encourages listening as much as looking.</p><p>A hidden gem waits near the end, an unassuming wall vitrine of letters, packing slips, and a folded map marked with pencilled routes. It reads like studio debris, yet it sharpens the stakes by tying each bundle and marking to a chain of handling and exchange. Nearby, a small cluster of numbered tags and twine fragments sits beside a terse checklist, each ticked line matching a visible scar in the cloth.</p>\n", 'max_output_tokens': 9000, 'model': 'gpt-5.2', 'reasoning': {'effort': 'medium'}, 'text': {'verbosity': 'low', 'format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'name': 'temp_translation_bundle', 'strict': True, 'schema': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'fr': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'es': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'it': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'ru': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}, 'zh-CN': {'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False, 'properties': {'name': {'type': 'string'}, 'short': {'type': 'string'}, 'long': {'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['name', 'short', 'long']}}, 'required': ['fr', 'es', 'it', 'ru', 'zh-CN']}}}}}
